node.text:
The Word of the Lord says God created man in His own image and called it good. God created a clear, powerful purpose for manhood. Men, true masculinity was built into your DNA. Yet for many people, it has been blurred by conflicting messages from the world around us. We live in a time where men are looking for the codebook to manhood.

At BraveCo Men's Conference, our hope is to answer your hard questions, get in the foxhole with you, restore the narrative of manhood, and release you into the masculinity you were born to carry.

Join us for our first-ever BraveCo Men’s Conference in partnership with Bethel Church, featuring speakers John Eldredge, Kris Vallotton, Brian Johnson, Danny Silk, Jason Vallotton, and Aaron Zint. This is not your typical Men’s Conference, but instead features opportunities to build a brotherhood as well as interactive experiences with professional horse trainer Todd Pierce, who will break a wild horse to demonstrate how Jesus pursues, heals, and becomes one with us as a Father.

Aug 25 - 27, 2021. Register now for in-person and online tickets at bethel.com/braveco

node.text:
BSSM pastors and worship teams want to minister to YOU!

You’re invited to a night exclusively for our local church members, to come worship and encounter the heart of God in a special Encounter Room for the Local Church.

During the school year, BSSM regularly hosts live times of prayer and worship streamed on YouTube for both students and the global BSSM family. These times have been presence-filled and powerful! This summer, they are seeking to create space to bless you. The first BSSM Encounter Room for Local Church in May was incredibly impactful. God loves to fill the room when His children show up in worship!

Worship will be led by Hannah Waters and David Funk, with ministry led by BSSM pastors on June 23rd at 6:30-8:00 PM in the College View Sanctuary. If you’re unable to attend, the event will also be publicly streamed to Youtube so you can watch on BSSM’s Youtube channel! (link in bio)
 
We hope to see you there. You won’t want to miss this beautiful time of worship and encountering the love of Jesus!

node.text:
We received a powerful, prophetic word just days before the lockdown began last year. In a season where planning a new campus for our global movement did not seem to make practical sense, we held on to God’s logic and His perfect timing. This was one of the many words from God that we declared over our church and community last year.  

But it is now a new season. We need to be ready for what’s on the horizon. God has confirmed that we need to build now for what is coming tomorrow. God, give us eyes to see and ears to always recognize Your voice! Let’s declare faith-filled prayers as we step into this new chapter together.

Learn more or make a gift at bethel.com/build

node.text:
Our hearts and prayers go out to our neighbors in Plumas County, California, where the Dixie Fire has been burning for the past two weeks. Please pray with us that this fire immediately ceases, for a shift in the weather pattern, and for protection for all who live in this area and first responders. Pray for rain. 

Our @bethelglobalresponse team is on the ground in Plumas County and mobilizing to serve communities affected by the Dixie Fire. Click the link in bio for more information.
